When the Iconic brand @Gillette truly supports my mission as a barber, it solidifies the value of our partnership. During the early years of my barbering career I have always envisioned  to serve my community and find ways to inspire the next generation of barbers but never would I have imagined that the world biggest razor brand would be standing right by my side while doing it. This past December I was given the opportunity to sponsor @empirebarbershop “Showcase 2” and share my excellent experience as a Gillette Barber Council member, host a raffle with 2 of the illest collaborations ( @bape , @bugatti ) and gift barbers with the new #gillettelabs set. Being partnered with a brand does not just mean free stuff , I believe that a true partnership includes both parties sharing specific goals and collaborating to help each other execute to achieve them. A huge s/o to @kikofranciscomedia for creating a masterpiece of a video #GilletteXJayR #gillettebarbercouncil

“Leave a Legacy to die a Legend” Another Skyline Barber College semester in the books. This second class was special. I had the opportunity to teach several unique individuals fresh out of high school  as well as others who were  inspired to choose this program to jump start their second or third career path. This class has taught me to be even more prepared in order to keep the level of interest constant. Each barber learns different which then challenged me to adjust my level of communication. But most importantly solidify everyone’s strengths and help improve areas that I seen lack to build confidence. These student’s always affirmed me on not just what I was teaching but how I taught each and everyone one of them. I can officially call the two graduating classes “my students” . #skylinecollege #barbercollege #barberprofessor #letstakeaninstructorpicture #zanderMVP

“Be interested vs. interesting” Grateful for the incredible chance during the Fall 2023 Semester at Skyline Community College to serve as the Keynote Speaker for CTE day (Career & Technical Education) and share insights on entrepreneurship with local high school students. It’s a privilege to have had the opportunity to impart my strategies and experiences from my barbering career, paving the way for partnerships, work in entertainment, engagements with high-profile clients, and the opportunity to educate locally and internationally. Speaking on that stage highlighted the importance of genuine connections, surrounding oneself with the right people, and defining my identity—an invaluable journey that propelled my life as an entrepreneur. S/o @dj_bitesize 🎧 for rocking the crowd and @castilltho 🎥for capturing the event through your lens  #skylinecollege #community #college #keynotespeaker #entrepreneurship
